HEADWORD: Machete
<hw>Ma*che"te</hw> <pr>(m⟦adot⟧*sh⟦ecr⟧t"⟦esl⟧; <it>Sp.</it>
m⟦adot⟧*ch⟦amac⟧"t⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>A
large heavy knife resembling a broadsword, often two or three feet in
length, -- used by the inhabitants of Spanish America as a hatchet to
cut their way through thickets, and for various other purposes.</def>
<rj><au>J. Stevens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> matchet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

